content.task: Lead the architectural consolidation of duplicate security types. We identified SecurityConfig exists in 3 files (stellar_security.py, stellar_config_models.py, stellar_security_types.py) and SecurityLevel in 2 files. Design the consolidation strategy to eliminate duplication while maintaining strict compliance with NEVER skipping failing tests.
content.context:
Architectural Consolidation - Priority 2:
- Target: SecurityConfig (3 duplicates), SecurityLevel (2 duplicates) 
- Files: stellar_security.py, stellar_config_models.py, stellar_security_types.py
- Goal: Single source of truth for security type definitions
- Compliance: NEVER skip failing tests, maintain backward compatibility
- Standards: Production-ready consolidation with comprehensive validation
- Pattern: Create canonical module, deprecate duplicates, update imports
